OL,3,CFirst minister apologises to victim of
OL,4,Cgrooming gangs in Scotland
OL,6,FThey say these are the same bodies who
OL,7,Flet them down in the first place and
OL,8,Fare calling for the government to
OL,9,Fappoint an independent chair of the
OL,10,Freview, similar to the role held by
OL,11,FBaroness Casey in England and Wales.
OL,13,FAfter Taylor, which is a pseudonym to
OL,14,Fprotect her identity, spoke out, the
OL,15,FFirst Minister invited her to Bute
OL,16,FHouse for a private in-person meeting.
OL,18,FWe spoke to her as she emerged.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
