OL,3,CFirst minister apologises to victim of
OL,4,Cgrooming gangs in Scotland
OL,6,FSandra Brown OBE, the head of the
OL,7,FMoira Anderson Foundation, a child
OL,8,Fprotection organisation, shares the
OL,9,Fvictim's concerns about the
OL,10,Findependence of the proposed review.
OL,12,F"Looking at the basic reports, you
OL,13,Frealise there is a closing of ranks
OL,14,Fgoing on, and I think that could
OL,15,Fhappen across inter-agencies.
OL,17,F"It's not helpful and we will not
OL,18,Flearn lessons or move on unless it is
OL,19,Fa completely unbiased independent
OL,20,Freview."
